WEBVTT

00:07.746 --> 00:09.922
Meredith: Since the early 1900s,

00:09.966 --> 00:14.188
morbidity and mortality
conferences, or "M&M"s,

00:14.231 --> 00:16.364
have helped surgeons learn
from cases

00:16.407 --> 00:18.888
where there was
a serious complication.

00:18.931 --> 00:21.021
Or a fatal outcome.No.

00:21.064 --> 00:24.154
♪ I'm going for show

00:24.198 --> 00:26.113
♪ Just give me
a beat and melody ♪

00:26.156 --> 00:31.683
During M&Ms, we assess both
systematic and personal errors.

00:31.727 --> 00:35.774
We review every step,
every decision.

00:35.818 --> 00:39.039
We get to the bottom of what
happened and how it happened.

00:39.082 --> 00:40.388
[ Knock on door ]Yeah?

00:40.431 --> 00:42.085
♪ I got this stage

00:42.129 --> 00:43.043
Room service.

00:43.086 --> 00:45.871
Hi.
Thank you.

00:45.915 --> 00:47.656
You, uh,
get your kids to school?

00:47.699 --> 00:49.223
I did.Good.

00:49.266 --> 00:50.746
They were
five minutes early.Mm-hmm.

00:50.789 --> 00:52.139
They're never
five minutes early.

00:52.182 --> 00:53.488
[ Chuckles ]
What's your day look like?

00:53.531 --> 00:55.403
Tedious.

00:55.446 --> 00:57.796
I have a follow-up with
Hamilton, and then I have

00:57.840 --> 01:00.538
to watch someone I really like
get interrogated in an M&M.

01:00.582 --> 01:03.193
Anything good?No, he avulsed the IMA

01:03.237 --> 01:05.326
right off the aorta
during an ileostomy takedown.

01:05.369 --> 01:06.892
Patient bled to death.

01:06.936 --> 01:08.111
And there was no attending
in the room.

01:08.155 --> 01:09.156
Oof.

01:09.199 --> 01:11.071
Yeah.
What time's your flight?

01:11.114 --> 01:12.724
I have to leave for the airport
in about 20 minutes.

01:12.768 --> 01:14.117
I wish you were staying.

01:14.161 --> 01:16.206
I have 20 minutes.

01:16.250 --> 01:18.469
♪ You know,
I'll seal your fate ♪

01:18.513 --> 01:22.386
We consider what we could have
done better or differently...

01:22.430 --> 01:23.735
Wow.

01:23.779 --> 01:25.389
♪ Uh-huh

01:25.433 --> 01:26.695
I know.
[ Chuckles ]

01:26.738 --> 01:28.392
[ Luna crying ]

01:28.436 --> 01:31.308
♪ Face present and I feel
something coming for ya ♪

01:31.352 --> 01:32.744
♪ Na-na-na-na-na

01:32.788 --> 01:34.833
Oh, you were right.

01:34.877 --> 01:37.793
[ Exhales deeply ]
This is fun.

01:37.836 --> 01:39.882
♪ Can't escape, but it's okay

01:39.925 --> 01:43.233
...and hope we never make
the same mistake ever again.

01:43.277 --> 01:44.756
♪ A hook and a verse

01:44.800 --> 01:45.975
♪ A couple of words

01:46.018 --> 01:47.542
♪ Watch me do this

01:47.585 --> 01:49.413
♪ Got it in your head

01:49.457 --> 01:51.023
Hey.

01:51.067 --> 01:53.025
Hey.
How was Mr. Yeyni's CABG?

01:53.069 --> 01:54.549
Oh, smooth. Yeah.

01:54.592 --> 01:55.941
Were you able to
talk to Richard?

01:55.985 --> 01:57.421
No.

01:57.465 --> 01:59.119
All he said when I asked him
about it was,

01:59.162 --> 02:01.121
"Save it for the M&M."

02:01.164 --> 02:02.513
Well, I mean,
he's not wrong.

02:02.557 --> 02:04.472
We are
a teaching hospital.

02:04.515 --> 02:06.865
I know M&M's are essential,
but I hate them.

02:06.909 --> 02:09.216
Both things are true.

02:11.740 --> 02:14.960
Woman over PA:
Dr. Manner to the E.R.
Dr. Manner to the E.R.

02:16.658 --> 02:18.616
Grey!
Here, take this.

02:18.660 --> 02:20.270
A ventral hernia repair.

02:20.314 --> 02:22.359
Patient's name is Franks.
1443.

02:22.403 --> 02:23.708
Wait.

02:23.752 --> 02:25.493
Right now?Yeah.

02:25.536 --> 02:27.451
What about the M&M?
A-Aren't I supposed to weigh in?

02:27.495 --> 02:30.411
No one else is available,
and I need to run the M&M,

02:30.454 --> 02:32.848
so unless you're
needed on a plane,

02:32.891 --> 02:34.371
I really need you
in O.R. 3.

02:34.415 --> 02:35.720
Okay.
I'm on it.Okay.

02:35.764 --> 02:37.592
But, you know,
go easy on Schmitt.

02:37.635 --> 02:40.072
I'm sure he's suffering enough,
and he's come a long way.

02:41.161 --> 02:43.641
He's still not here yet.
Where is he?

02:43.685 --> 02:45.904
I don't know.Doesn't he live with you?

02:45.948 --> 02:48.646
I don't put GPS locators
on my roommates, do you?No need to be rude.

02:48.690 --> 02:50.387
Do you think you'll have
to go up there? Since
you were in the room?

02:50.431 --> 02:51.693
Hey,
where's Schmitt?

02:51.736 --> 02:53.129
I don't know!Okay.

02:53.173 --> 02:55.871
[ People murmuring ]

03:00.702 --> 03:02.660
[ Sighs ]

03:05.359 --> 03:09.841
Okay, we all have
surgeries and clinic,

03:09.885 --> 03:12.104
so I'm gonna go ahead
and get started.

03:12.148 --> 03:16.021
Um, ask questions as they arise.

03:16.065 --> 03:18.763
Keep them constructive.
We are a teaching hospital.

03:18.807 --> 03:21.157
This is how we learn.

03:21.201 --> 03:24.334
Dr. Schmitt
will be presenting...

03:25.422 --> 03:28.599
Uh...

03:28.643 --> 03:32.908
Okay, so, our first case is
colorectal surgery service.

03:32.951 --> 03:34.779
26 year-old male...

03:34.823 --> 03:38.479
♪♪

03:38.522 --> 03:39.567
Dr. Schmitt.

03:39.610 --> 03:46.704
♪♪

03:46.748 --> 03:53.885
♪♪

03:53.929 --> 04:00.936
♪♪

04:00.979 --> 04:03.721
The case is a 26-year-old male

04:03.765 --> 04:05.245
with history
of ulcerative colitis.

04:12.730 --> 04:15.690
...at which point,
we were about ready to proceed

04:15.733 --> 04:17.735
with stapling the anastomosis,

04:17.779 --> 04:21.870
but I felt that I needed better
exposure of the small bowel,

04:21.913 --> 04:24.481
so I reached into the cavity.

04:28.442 --> 04:30.705
Questions are not encouraged --
They're required.

04:32.010 --> 04:34.361
Dr. Wright,
ask a question.

04:34.404 --> 04:36.276
Um...

04:36.319 --> 04:39.279
Uh, had you observed
any bleeding at that point?

04:39.322 --> 04:41.281
No.Did you have
good visualization

04:41.324 --> 04:42.804
on what you were
putting traction on?

04:42.847 --> 04:44.066
I believed I did.

04:45.415 --> 04:46.895
Okay.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.029
[ Sighs ]

04:51.073 --> 04:53.293
At that point,
everything was dry

04:53.336 --> 04:55.686
and ready for anastomosis.

04:55.730 --> 04:58.080
As stated, the patient...[ Bird chirping]

04:58.123 --> 04:59.734
Devon: It's been so long since
I've seen a waterfall in person.

04:59.777 --> 05:02.563
Dr. Schmitt?
Dr. Schmitt?

05:02.606 --> 05:04.304
Continue.

05:06.480 --> 05:10.658
Um, [clears throat]
everything was dry and, um...

05:10.701 --> 05:16.185
the field was clean,
so I asked for the GIA stapler.

05:16.228 --> 05:17.969
But there was --

05:18.013 --> 05:19.623
Um...

05:19.667 --> 05:21.016
[ Clears throat ]

05:21.059 --> 05:23.627
There, uh --
There was no indication

05:23.671 --> 05:28.023
of any abnormal anatomy or
friable structures, right?

05:28.066 --> 05:29.416
That you could see,
I mean.

05:29.459 --> 05:30.939
[ Bird chirping]What?

05:30.982 --> 05:32.854
[ Muffled ] Meaning you
couldn't have predicted

05:32.897 --> 05:34.725
that the aorta was
gonna rupture...

05:34.769 --> 05:36.771
This is just the best.

05:36.814 --> 05:38.425
Yeah. I'm gonna stay here
awhile, you guys.

05:38.468 --> 05:41.341
It was an unanticipated
complication.

05:41.384 --> 05:43.604
Is there a question in there
somewhere, Helm?

05:43.647 --> 05:44.909
I didn't think so.

05:45.954 --> 05:47.695
Schmitt, go.

05:47.738 --> 05:51.873
Uh, that -- that was the...

05:51.916 --> 05:56.312
the f-- the field, it filled
with blood, and, um...

05:56.356 --> 05:58.749
I'm -- I'm sorry.

05:58.793 --> 06:00.969
Levi:
You're Devon Gomez.Devon: Never knew
I had a groupie.

06:01.012 --> 06:02.013
It's nice to meet you,
Dr. Schmitt.

06:02.057 --> 06:03.841
Bailey:
Schmitt, call it.

06:03.885 --> 06:06.278
[ Quietly ] I killed Devon.
I, uh...

06:06.322 --> 06:09.369
I just -- I killed him.
He's dead.

06:09.412 --> 06:11.632
Dr. Schmitt,
look, we are here --

06:11.675 --> 06:13.198
Dr. Schmitt, no, no.

06:13.242 --> 06:15.897
We are here to determine
what ha-- and how to --

06:19.466 --> 06:21.729
Hey, no, no, no!
The M&M isn't finished.

06:21.772 --> 06:24.514
Um, un-until
Dr. Schmitt returns,

06:24.558 --> 06:26.864
Dr. Webber
will take the questions.

06:32.479 --> 06:34.219
If Dr. Schmitt was
the primary surgeon

06:34.263 --> 06:37.005
and you're the attending,
who's in charge?

06:37.048 --> 06:39.921
The Webber Method dictates
that a resident cannot go on

06:39.964 --> 06:41.313
to the next step
in the procedure

06:41.357 --> 06:42.750
without an attending
being present.

06:42.793 --> 06:45.013
Yeah, I-I understand
what the method is, sir.

06:45.056 --> 06:46.971
I'm just not sure I understand
the chain of command.

06:47.015 --> 06:48.451
I beg your pardon?

06:48.495 --> 06:49.844
Well, I mean, the --
the Webber Method

06:49.887 --> 06:51.411
seems to rotate authority
during surgery

06:51.454 --> 06:53.021
depending on
which step you're on,

06:53.064 --> 06:55.937
which, with all due respect,
sir, seems...confusing.

06:55.980 --> 06:57.591
Perhaps a little more time
in our program

06:57.634 --> 06:59.462
would help clear up
any confusion.

06:59.506 --> 07:01.029
Alright, let's get back
to the next question, please.

07:01.072 --> 07:02.726
In a Webber Method surgery,
can you just remind us

07:02.770 --> 07:05.468
what exactly happens
if a complication arises,

07:05.512 --> 07:07.644
even if it's not at
the predetermined step

07:07.688 --> 07:09.646
when an attending
would need to be called?

07:09.690 --> 07:11.169
Well, an attending
should be called anyway.

07:11.213 --> 07:13.476
Right, but for all
intents and purposes,

07:13.520 --> 07:16.261
your method sets up
these senior residents

07:16.305 --> 07:18.263
asthe attendings,
right?

07:18.307 --> 07:20.352
Didn't you specifically
use the word "attendings"

07:20.396 --> 07:22.746
when you first
introduced the method?

07:22.790 --> 07:24.444
"Today you will be
the attendings." ...you will be the attendings.

07:24.487 --> 07:26.750
Welcome to the Webber Method.

07:28.360 --> 07:30.275
[ Maggie
clears throat ]

07:30.319 --> 07:33.235
Dr. Webber, was there ever
a meeting of department heads

07:33.278 --> 07:35.237
to discuss whether
we should adopt

07:35.280 --> 07:37.457
this particular
teaching style?

07:37.500 --> 07:39.023
Does that
make a difference?

07:39.067 --> 07:40.329
Well, yes, I mean,
we have meetings to discuss

07:40.372 --> 07:41.678
what brand of sutures
we're going to buy.

07:41.722 --> 07:43.158
Why not meet about this?

07:43.201 --> 07:44.986
Are other hospitals using this,
Catherine?

07:45.029 --> 07:46.901
Other
foundation hospitals?

07:46.944 --> 07:49.425
Michelle: Dr. Webber is your
chief medical officer, Dr. Fox.

07:49.469 --> 07:50.905
The method's
named after him.

07:50.948 --> 07:52.515
You never considered
that there would be

07:52.559 --> 07:54.517
negative consequences
or a P.R. nightmare?

07:54.561 --> 07:56.867
Dr. Lin, you recently
promoted the Webber Method

07:56.911 --> 07:58.826
while recruiting
new residents.

07:58.869 --> 08:00.262
This is a teaching tool,
my dear,

08:00.305 --> 08:02.264
not some risky
cure for cancer.

08:02.307 --> 08:04.962
It's a teaching tool that
cost a patient their life.

08:05.006 --> 08:07.356
Dr. Bailey,
you initially

08:07.399 --> 08:09.184
expressed reservations
about the method.

08:09.227 --> 08:10.707
What changed for you?

08:10.751 --> 08:12.927
Is the M&M on the patient
or the Webber Method?

08:12.970 --> 08:14.276
Because the method
didn't hold the scalpel.

08:14.319 --> 08:15.973
Thank you.

08:16.017 --> 08:18.541
Well, there are clearly
residents who are not ready.

08:18.585 --> 08:20.717
Michelle: What about
the American Board of Surgery?

08:20.761 --> 08:22.719
Have they
sanctioned it?Everybody, just please.

08:22.763 --> 08:24.808
Dr. Webber is just prioritizing
our education.

08:24.852 --> 08:27.158
-We're here to learn.
-Okay, everyone.

08:27.202 --> 08:28.551
Why would they weigh in on a
method for general procedure?

08:28.595 --> 08:30.684
We need to get back
to asking questions.

08:30.727 --> 08:31.728
-What they need to approve...
-This hospital...

08:31.772 --> 08:34.514
Here we go.
[ Groans ]

08:34.557 --> 08:36.167
[ Grunts ]

08:36.211 --> 08:37.386
How's the pain?

08:37.429 --> 08:38.300
It's okay.
It's not terrible.

08:38.343 --> 08:39.736
Good.

08:48.049 --> 08:49.703
[ Door closes ]Listen, Owen,

08:49.746 --> 08:51.487
I-I know that
you have gone through

08:51.531 --> 08:54.316
something horrible,
and I've given it two days,

08:54.359 --> 08:55.839
but now I'm gonna
sit here until you tell me

08:55.883 --> 08:57.493
what the hell
is going on.

08:57.537 --> 08:58.973
Noah's wife
has called the house

08:59.016 --> 09:00.191
several times
looking for you.

09:00.235 --> 09:01.758
Why?
Teddy --

09:01.802 --> 09:03.673
Owen, after everything
that we've been through,

09:03.717 --> 09:06.589
after 20 years,
I deserve the truth.

09:06.633 --> 09:08.809
What does Heather want?
Why did Hayes quit?

09:08.852 --> 09:11.072
I know that something
happened in the car.

09:11.115 --> 09:13.596
Can you just tell me,
please?

09:13.640 --> 09:17.382
You're right.
Something happened in the car.

09:17.426 --> 09:19.776
But, Teddy, I'm asking you
to trust me.

09:19.820 --> 09:21.256
I can't tell you.

09:21.299 --> 09:23.867
[ Scoffs ]

09:23.911 --> 09:25.608
What about me?
Don't I deserve the same?

09:25.652 --> 09:27.088
Doesn't trust
go both ways?

09:27.131 --> 09:29.003
Of course, but --Owen, it's me.

09:29.046 --> 09:30.265
You can sit there as long
as you want, okay?

09:30.308 --> 09:31.266
But I'm not
gonna tell you.

09:32.528 --> 09:34.704
I love you.

09:34.748 --> 09:36.576
But I can't.

09:36.619 --> 09:37.925
You can.

09:37.968 --> 09:39.666
But you won't.

09:39.709 --> 09:42.146
Okay, I won't.

09:42.190 --> 09:44.279
[ Chuckles ]

09:44.322 --> 09:48.022
♪♪

09:53.070 --> 09:56.291
Legal hasn't heard anything
from the Gomez family.

09:56.334 --> 09:59.163
We may avoid a lawsuit
altogether.

09:59.207 --> 10:01.775
Hmm.
But you still have some
decisions to make.

10:01.818 --> 10:04.038
Ihave some
decisions to make?

10:04.081 --> 10:07.824
He's my husband, Dr. Bailey,
but this is yourhospital.

10:07.868 --> 10:10.000
The method was successful

10:10.044 --> 10:11.872
as long as the residents
stuck to it.

10:11.915 --> 10:14.439
But surgical residents are
not known for their humility,

10:14.483 --> 10:16.790
so whether or not
the method continues on

10:16.833 --> 10:20.402
after this suspension,
it's up to you.

10:20.445 --> 10:23.057
Woman over P.A.:
Dr. O'Dell to the ICU.
Dr. O'Dell...

10:23.100 --> 10:25.407
Hey, ventral hernia's
repaired.

10:25.450 --> 10:27.235
How was the M&M?

10:27.278 --> 10:29.237
I want to check in on Richard
before my VIP's scans.

10:29.280 --> 10:30.542
The M&M was awful.

10:30.586 --> 10:32.196
Richard needs space.

10:32.240 --> 10:33.763
But I put you down for

10:33.807 --> 10:36.897
a Roux-en-Y hepaticojejunostomy
in O.R. 4.

10:36.940 --> 10:39.464
Oh, well, I've already
over-scheduled my own day.

10:39.508 --> 10:41.118
I want to help you,
but I can't --

10:41.162 --> 10:42.859
Look at my face.
This is a desperate face.

10:42.903 --> 10:44.905
This is
a-a begging face.

10:44.948 --> 10:46.471
I'm desperate
and I'm begging,

10:46.515 --> 10:48.604
and I'm asking for
your help, Grey.

10:48.648 --> 10:52.521
Look, I'm down a trauma surgeon,
a cardio surgeon,

10:52.564 --> 10:54.697
a peds surgeon,
and now a resident

10:54.741 --> 10:57.047
'cause Schmitt walked out.

10:57.091 --> 10:59.746
And t-the rest of them
are so traumatized

10:59.789 --> 11:02.270
that they'll probably
need a safe space

11:02.313 --> 11:04.272
and a week off
to feel their feelings.

11:04.315 --> 11:07.144
Okay.
I can take the hepatico-J.

11:07.188 --> 11:08.842
And I know someone
who can do the hernia repair.

11:10.626 --> 11:12.367
Ideally, a surgeon.
Uh-huh.

11:12.410 --> 11:12.976
Hi.

11:15.936 --> 11:17.328
Hey. You okay?

11:17.372 --> 11:19.548
You kinda went after
Richard in the M&M.

11:19.591 --> 11:20.941
I went after the method.

11:20.984 --> 11:22.899
Right, but the Webber Method
is Richard.

11:22.943 --> 11:24.684
Do you still stand by it?

11:24.727 --> 11:27.382
The Webber Method? After
everything that we just heard?

11:27.425 --> 11:29.645
We don't use it in
our department,

11:29.689 --> 11:31.168
so I'm not really
sure that I can --

11:31.212 --> 11:33.649
I know that you respect Richard.
We all do.

11:33.693 --> 11:36.086
It's why I wanted to speak
to him before the M&M.

11:36.130 --> 11:38.306
Maggie, the method works.

11:38.349 --> 11:40.003
You just haven't
been around to see it.Exactly.

11:40.047 --> 11:41.918
I haven't been around,
and I come back

11:41.962 --> 11:43.746
and Richard's new
teaching method

11:43.790 --> 11:45.313
has gotten someone killed,

11:45.356 --> 11:47.924
and no one is being honest
with him about it.

11:47.968 --> 11:51.319
So, you respect him,
but I love him,

11:51.362 --> 11:53.800
so I'm gonna keep
telling him the truth.

11:53.843 --> 11:55.105
Okay?
Okay.

11:55.149 --> 11:56.541
[ Cellphone ringing ]

11:56.585 --> 11:58.543
[ Sighs ]
I gotta take this.

11:58.587 --> 11:59.980
Alright.

12:04.071 --> 12:05.550
Thank you, Carla.

12:05.594 --> 12:08.510
Hey, um, have you
seen Levi anywhere?

12:08.553 --> 12:09.772
No one has seen him
since the M&M.

12:09.816 --> 12:11.992
No, I've been swamped
all morning.

12:12.035 --> 12:14.951
Oh, uh, I might have
a double arthroplasty later.

12:14.995 --> 12:16.518
You want in?

12:16.561 --> 12:19.826
Films show major scar tissue,
so it should be fun.

12:19.869 --> 12:21.349
Things better with
you and Shepherd?

12:21.392 --> 12:23.003
Uh, no.

12:23.046 --> 12:25.701
But...I feel great.

12:25.745 --> 12:28.965
Dr. Burkes to oncology.
Dr. Burkes to oncology.

12:29.009 --> 12:30.532
Hello.

12:30.575 --> 12:32.186
I'm Dr. Lincoln.
What seems to be going on?

12:32.229 --> 12:33.622
Uh, Ms. Hanley.

12:33.665 --> 12:35.276
Second grade science teacher.

12:35.319 --> 12:36.494
Wish she had been mine.

12:36.538 --> 12:38.061
Please, call me Lila.

12:38.105 --> 12:40.107
Not even my students
call me Ms. Hanley.

12:40.150 --> 12:42.413
Anyway, uh,
my leg's numbed up again.

12:42.457 --> 12:44.024
I've got shooting pains
right below the knee.

12:44.067 --> 12:46.113
But this time
when it happened,

12:46.156 --> 12:48.071
I barely made it down
the staircase at the IMAX.

12:48.115 --> 12:49.507
Northwest Science Center.

12:49.551 --> 12:51.118
We go every year
during winter camp.

12:51.161 --> 12:52.815
X-rays show
some minimal changes

12:52.859 --> 12:54.295
indicative
of osteoarthritis.

12:54.338 --> 12:55.818
Okay.
Uh, you said "this time."

12:55.862 --> 12:57.037
This has happened before?

12:57.080 --> 12:58.603
It's happened
a couple times.

12:58.647 --> 13:00.040
Cortisone shot
usually does the trick,

13:00.083 --> 13:01.824
but now my leg's
a little off.

13:01.868 --> 13:03.434
And no allergic reaction
to the cortisone?

13:03.478 --> 13:04.827
No.

13:04.871 --> 13:06.481
Okay.

13:06.524 --> 13:08.004
Perez here will do
a work-up on your knee,

13:08.048 --> 13:09.440
and we'll see if we can
get you that shot.

13:09.484 --> 13:12.008
Uh...

13:13.444 --> 13:15.142
Morning, Francesca.[ Exhales deeply ]

13:15.185 --> 13:17.057
I would say it's
good to see you,

13:17.100 --> 13:18.885
but I really wish
I wasn't back here.

13:18.928 --> 13:20.321
We're gonna figure out why.

13:20.364 --> 13:21.496
Tseng?

13:21.539 --> 13:23.411
Francesca Lyons, 26.

13:23.454 --> 13:25.761
Complains of continued pain
in the lower back.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.937
Treated for pain from
mildly herniated discs

13:27.981 --> 13:29.852
with an epidural injection
three weeks ago

13:29.896 --> 13:31.201
and another
six weeks ago.

13:31.245 --> 13:32.855
Do you mind if
I take a look?

13:34.422 --> 13:37.120
Has the pain been consistent
since your last injection?

13:37.164 --> 13:39.166
I felt great during
the first week.

13:39.209 --> 13:41.690
I hiked in Discovery Park,
I biked around the waterfront,

13:41.733 --> 13:43.039
and I got back on Bumble.

13:43.083 --> 13:45.172
Sounds very busy.

13:45.215 --> 13:47.174
I started having sex again,
but the pain just came back,

13:47.217 --> 13:49.176
same as the time before.

13:49.219 --> 13:52.962
And now I am on my period, so
I have horrible cramps and this.

13:53.006 --> 13:55.312
Tseng, would you call
for a GYN consult?

13:55.356 --> 13:57.706
Perfect. Lady problems.

13:57.749 --> 14:00.056
That won't be embarrassing to
bring up with my new boyfriend.

14:00.100 --> 14:01.536
Hiker or biker?Neither.

14:01.579 --> 14:03.320
He's got a boat,
which normally I hate

14:03.364 --> 14:05.366
because sharks
are close to boats.

14:05.409 --> 14:07.716
But I'd be willing to suck it up
because he is so, so hot.

14:07.759 --> 14:09.457
He is shark-risk hot.

14:09.500 --> 14:11.459
He wants to cruise around
Puget Sound next week,

14:11.502 --> 14:13.591
and I want to
have sex on a boat.

14:13.635 --> 14:15.419
We will see what
we can do.
[ Chuckles ]

14:16.551 --> 14:18.205
Hayes! Hey.

14:18.248 --> 14:19.380
I've been
looking for you.

14:19.423 --> 14:21.295
Do you have a second?

14:21.338 --> 14:22.644
Sure.

14:22.687 --> 14:24.646
So, I heard you quit.

14:24.689 --> 14:25.865
I have some cases
to hand off.

14:25.908 --> 14:28.128
But, uh...yeah.

14:28.171 --> 14:30.130
Bailey can't
lose you right now.

14:30.173 --> 14:31.653
I know.

14:31.696 --> 14:33.220
Well, I've been
trying to call you.

14:33.263 --> 14:35.439
It's been pretty hectic
getting the boys packed up.

14:35.483 --> 14:36.658
So, what?

14:36.701 --> 14:38.181
Your whole life flashed
before your eyes

14:38.225 --> 14:40.270
and you realized you're unhappy
here and need to quit?

14:40.314 --> 14:42.185
Something like that.

14:42.229 --> 14:43.795
And your plan was to leave
without saying goodbye?

14:43.839 --> 14:45.188
Yeah.

14:45.232 --> 14:47.060
Why?

14:48.844 --> 14:50.977
Because if I said goodbye
to you, Grey,

14:51.020 --> 14:52.761
I might not
actually leave.

14:52.804 --> 14:55.720
♪♪

14:55.764 --> 14:57.244
In all the years
since Abigail died,

14:57.287 --> 15:00.987
you're the first person
who got it.

15:01.030 --> 15:03.946
You made me
feel less alone.

15:03.990 --> 15:05.252
You helped me believe

15:05.295 --> 15:07.819
there might even be life
after Abigail.

15:09.517 --> 15:11.127
Thank you for that.

15:11.171 --> 15:15.827
♪♪

15:15.871 --> 15:17.220
Take care.

15:17.264 --> 15:18.439
You too.

15:18.482 --> 15:22.573
♪♪

15:28.666 --> 15:29.841
Hi, Francesca.

15:29.885 --> 15:31.931
I'm Dr. DeLuca,
and this is Dr. Wilson.

15:31.974 --> 15:33.889
Hi, there.
Hi.

15:33.933 --> 15:35.282
You're gonna stay with me,
right?

15:35.325 --> 15:37.980
Of course. Yeah, we're gonna
figure this out together.

15:38.024 --> 15:39.895
So, I treated Francesca
for back pain

15:39.939 --> 15:41.984
and minor degenerative
disc disease,

15:42.028 --> 15:43.855
but her pain coincides
with her period,

15:43.899 --> 15:46.510
she's on oral contraceptives,
and she has pain with sex.

15:46.554 --> 15:48.469
Okay, yeah, okay.

15:48.512 --> 15:50.950
Um, thank you, Dr. Shepherd.
[ Chuckles ]

15:52.386 --> 15:54.910
Francesca, would you mind
if Dr. Wilson examines you?

15:54.954 --> 15:56.651
Go for it.
Thank you.

15:56.694 --> 15:59.959
Okay, um...so how long

16:00.002 --> 16:03.049
have you been having severe pain
with your periods?

16:03.092 --> 16:05.877
Since I was the girl
sitting on the bleachers

16:05.921 --> 16:07.836
for half the month
during P.E.

16:07.879 --> 16:10.665
Nothing like 30 eighth graders
knowing your menstrual cycle.

16:10.708 --> 16:12.362
Okay, you're gonna feel
a little pressure, okay?

16:14.190 --> 16:16.758
Ahh! Ooh.

16:16.801 --> 16:19.369
Has you ever been evaluated
for endometriosis?Mnh-mnh.

16:19.413 --> 16:22.068
It's when the cells that line
the inside of the uterus

16:22.111 --> 16:24.592
grow outside the uterus,
and in some cases,

16:24.635 --> 16:26.942
the tissue can accumulate
in one space.

16:26.986 --> 16:28.813
Now, that would also
explain the back pain,

16:28.857 --> 16:30.424
if that's where
the tissue built up.

16:30.467 --> 16:31.816
A little pressure.

16:31.860 --> 16:33.122
Okay,
the good thing is,

16:33.166 --> 16:36.517
if it is that,
then it is treatable.

16:36.560 --> 16:38.432
When do we start,
and how long is recovery?

16:38.475 --> 16:40.129
We'll schedule
a diagnostic surgery,

16:40.173 --> 16:43.045
and if endometriosis is present,
we'll do what we can

16:43.089 --> 16:45.047
to try and remove it
when you're ready.

16:45.091 --> 16:47.528
The sooner the better.
I've got things to do.

16:47.571 --> 16:50.357
And by "things,"
I mean my new boyfriend.

16:50.400 --> 16:53.751
[ Chuckles ] Never underestimate
the value of pain-free sex.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.971
Let's see if we can
get it done today.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.190
Yeah.

16:57.233 --> 16:59.888
♪♪

16:59.931 --> 17:01.716
Okay.
Privileges received.

17:01.759 --> 17:03.022
Pays to have an in,
I guess.

17:03.065 --> 17:04.066
Thank for coming back.

17:04.110 --> 17:05.720
Sure.

17:05.763 --> 17:07.200
You're saving our sanity.Yes.

17:07.243 --> 17:08.679
And a man's life,
of course.
Of course.

17:08.723 --> 17:10.812
Okay. What do we got?45-year-old man

17:10.855 --> 17:12.857
with a right-sided
direct inguinal hernia.

17:12.901 --> 17:14.816
Okay.
Five months of pain.

17:14.859 --> 17:15.860
Booked for
an open repair.

17:15.904 --> 17:17.993
Okay, got it.
And what do you have?

17:18.037 --> 17:19.690
Hepatico-J.

17:19.734 --> 17:21.214
Sorta feels like
you took the fun one.

17:21.257 --> 17:23.129
I would never do that.
Never?

17:23.172 --> 17:24.347
Have fun.
You're going to O.R. 3.

17:24.391 --> 17:28.873
Okay. O.R. 3.

17:28.917 --> 17:30.397
You're gonna need
scrubs first.

17:30.440 --> 17:31.659
Oh. Thank God.

17:31.702 --> 17:34.314
[ Elevator bell dings ]

17:34.357 --> 17:38.709
Nurse Hazard to the O.R.
Nurse Hazard to the O.R.

17:39.623 --> 17:41.712
Construction accident.
Something with a circular saw.

17:41.756 --> 17:43.062
I believe she just
needs sutures,

17:43.105 --> 17:44.280
but there could be
debris inside.

17:44.324 --> 17:46.021
Okay,
have we gotten an X-ray,

17:46.065 --> 17:47.153
cleaned out
and examined the wound?

17:47.196 --> 17:49.285
No.

17:49.329 --> 17:52.201
I'm waiting for the twist in the
story as for why you haven't.

17:52.245 --> 17:54.464
I-I thought you'd want to
examine her first.

17:55.770 --> 17:57.076
Just in case, you know?

17:57.119 --> 17:59.904
Or you could observe
while I do the exam.

17:59.948 --> 18:02.907
I-I wanted to make sure
that I was doing it right.

18:02.951 --> 18:04.648
Well, you haven't done anything,
so how could it be wrong?

18:06.607 --> 18:08.870
X-ray, irrigation,
lap tray now!
Okay, yeah.

18:08.913 --> 18:09.958
Wha...

18:10.001 --> 18:13.962
Nurse Cline, extension 2219.

18:14.005 --> 18:15.572
Perez, what's Lila
still doing here?

18:15.616 --> 18:16.791
She wanted
a cortisone injection.

18:16.834 --> 18:18.097
Uh, that's why
I paged you.

18:18.140 --> 18:19.707
I think she also
needs an MRI.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.143
I was thinking
it might be --

18:21.187 --> 18:23.363
Um, Lila?

18:23.406 --> 18:26.105
Will you show me exactly
where it hurts?

18:29.543 --> 18:30.805
It's along there.

18:30.848 --> 18:33.416
The cortisone shot
should help,

18:33.460 --> 18:35.505
but if you're looking for
a more permanent solution,

18:35.549 --> 18:37.116
you might try
losing a little weight.

18:38.160 --> 18:40.162
I might try
losing a little weight?

18:40.206 --> 18:42.469
Maybe start with some
good walks with a friend

18:42.512 --> 18:43.687
and build up to more.

18:43.731 --> 18:46.212
I've been on
a diet since 1992,

18:46.255 --> 18:49.171
and I get a serious workout
every day chasing 8-year-olds.

18:49.215 --> 18:51.695
How am I supposed to take
"good walks with friends"

18:51.739 --> 18:54.133
when I have shooting pains
coming from my knee when I walk?

18:54.176 --> 18:56.178
All I'm saying is,
you might be surprised

18:56.222 --> 18:58.572
what even 10 to 15 pounds can do
to exacerbate joint pain.

18:58.615 --> 19:00.095
Got it.

19:00.139 --> 19:03.098
So if I just figure out
how not to be fat,

19:03.142 --> 19:04.926
all my problems
will magically go away.

19:04.969 --> 19:06.101
Thank you.

19:07.233 --> 19:09.496
Zero stars.

19:10.236 --> 19:11.193
Lila...

19:12.586 --> 19:16.198
Oh, I'm sorry, Lila.
Wait, uh...

19:16.242 --> 19:17.678
It looks like you might
have foot drop,

19:17.721 --> 19:19.810
based on the way
you're walking.
Have what?

19:19.854 --> 19:21.203
Uh, a foot drop
is something that

19:21.247 --> 19:24.206
losing a solid 10 to 15 pounds
will not fix.

19:24.250 --> 19:26.426
Would you like me to
order the MRI now, sir?

19:26.469 --> 19:28.210
Walking there might help me
build up to more.

19:28.254 --> 19:30.343
♪♪

19:30.386 --> 19:32.171
Thank you.

19:32.214 --> 19:33.259
Thank you.

19:35.957 --> 19:38.438
Teddy: Hayes, please.Hayes: Altman, I can't.

19:38.481 --> 19:41.745
We almost died together, and
y-you can't return a phone call?

19:41.789 --> 19:43.834
[ Sighs ]
What happened?

19:43.878 --> 19:45.358
Please, can you just --
can you just tell me?

19:45.401 --> 19:47.098
Talk to your husband.

19:47.142 --> 19:48.970
I am talking to my husband,
but he's not talking to me!

19:49.013 --> 19:51.146
There was something wrong
with Owen even before
he got in that car.

19:51.190 --> 19:52.756
I felt it.
I feelit.

19:52.800 --> 19:54.541
And if you've loved Owen
as long as I have loved him,

19:54.584 --> 19:56.325
you feel when
he's lying to you.

19:56.369 --> 19:58.806
You -- You -- You feel
your stomach turn to ice.

19:58.849 --> 20:01.374
And now he's hurt, and
I know he's in so much pain,

20:01.417 --> 20:03.463
but I have this horrible feeling
in my whole body,

20:03.506 --> 20:06.205
so can you please tell me
what happened in that car?

20:10.600 --> 20:13.560
He told me
to get out first.

20:13.603 --> 20:16.215
He told me to
think about my kids.

20:16.258 --> 20:19.609
And for that,
I'll always be in his debt.

20:19.653 --> 20:22.264
It's a miracle he survived.
I might not have.

20:22.308 --> 20:25.876
Thanks to your husband,
I got to get home to my kids.

20:25.920 --> 20:28.575
Thanks to your husband,
I -- I get to

20:28.618 --> 20:30.098
bring them back
to my family in Ireland.

20:30.141 --> 20:32.274
They get the chance to --
to build a new life.

20:32.318 --> 20:35.016
But why? Why are you
building a new life?

20:35.059 --> 20:37.192
Hayes, I see you at work.

20:37.236 --> 20:40.195
It's not like you
just to quit without notice.

20:40.239 --> 20:44.199
So whatever he did or whatever
he said to you must be so big

20:44.243 --> 20:46.070
that you're willing to
uproot your whole life.

20:46.114 --> 20:48.203
And for that,
I am -- I am so sorry.

20:48.247 --> 20:49.857
My kids and I have been
uprooted long before

20:49.900 --> 20:51.467
I got in that car
with you and Owen.

20:54.557 --> 20:56.994
Your husband's alive.

20:57.038 --> 20:58.257
Try to hold on to that.

21:00.476 --> 21:02.217
Goodbye, Altman.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.263
[ Sighs ]

21:04.306 --> 21:05.481
[ Car door closes ]

21:12.314 --> 21:14.142
♪♪

21:14.185 --> 21:16.623
[ Sighs ]

21:16.666 --> 21:19.234
[ Door opens ]

21:19.278 --> 21:27.460
♪♪

21:27.503 --> 21:28.809
I'd like to be alone.

21:28.852 --> 21:29.810
I know you would.

21:33.074 --> 21:36.469
Richard, I know you know
how traumatizing it is

21:36.512 --> 21:40.864
for a surgeon to lose a patient
due to an honest mistake.

21:40.908 --> 21:43.998
Yeah, I do.
So do you.

21:44.041 --> 21:46.435
Do you remember what
happened to my niece?

21:46.479 --> 21:48.002
Sabie?

21:48.045 --> 21:49.525
Yeah, you're right.
You're right.

21:49.569 --> 21:53.834
Um...it's because of Sabie that
I know how agonizing it is

21:53.877 --> 21:58.534
for a family to lose a loved one
due to a surgical error,

21:58.578 --> 22:01.276
especially one that
could have been prevented.

22:01.320 --> 22:03.626
You publicly humiliated me
in the hospital

22:03.670 --> 22:05.976
where I've worked
for over 30 years --

22:06.020 --> 22:07.369
Richard, that was
not my intention.

22:07.413 --> 22:08.936
I was just trying
to do my job.

22:10.546 --> 22:12.592
[ Sighs ]
I took an oath --

22:12.635 --> 22:13.984
I took the same damn oath!

22:14.028 --> 22:15.682
Now, Schmitt
didn't make a mistake.

22:15.725 --> 22:17.640
Schmitt made a decision,
okay?

22:17.684 --> 22:19.425
He chose to subvert
my teaching method.

22:19.468 --> 22:21.514
He chose to proceed
without waiting,

22:21.557 --> 22:24.778
and then, somehow,
you went after me?!

22:24.821 --> 22:27.258
I believe in systems,
okay?

22:27.302 --> 22:30.174
I believe in scientific data,
of running scenarios

22:30.218 --> 22:32.916
multiple times
to ensure they work

22:32.960 --> 22:35.049
before we implement
new procedures,

22:35.092 --> 22:36.964
and I-I don't believe that
we have done that here.

22:37.007 --> 22:39.488
We?
W-W-W-Who is "we," Maggie?

22:39.532 --> 22:41.272
You haven't been here.

22:41.316 --> 22:43.927
Neither has Meredith, so
neither of you get an opinion.

22:43.971 --> 22:46.016
So please leave me alone

22:46.060 --> 22:47.975
before I say something
that I'll regret!

22:48.018 --> 22:53.154
♪♪

22:53.197 --> 22:58.594
♪♪

22:58.638 --> 23:01.423
Carina:
What do the classic lesions
of endometriosis look like?

23:01.467 --> 23:05.209
Most commonly, they have
a blue-black appearance...

23:05.253 --> 23:07.777
like right there.

23:07.821 --> 23:10.519
Nice catch, Dr. Wilson.

23:10.563 --> 23:12.042
We'll get a biopsy
to confirm.

23:12.086 --> 23:13.435
Amelia: Hey.
How's she doing?

23:13.479 --> 23:16.395
Hey. I thought
you had a consult.

23:16.438 --> 23:17.874
I-I finished.

23:17.918 --> 23:19.267
Wilson, can you
pull the scope back?

23:19.310 --> 23:20.573
Yeah, sorry.

23:20.616 --> 23:22.575
Are those all lesions?Yes.

23:22.618 --> 23:25.795
Here and here by
the uterosacral ligament,

23:25.839 --> 23:27.231
which explains
the back pain

23:27.275 --> 23:29.320
and also why
your epidurals didn't work.

23:29.364 --> 23:31.018
We'll get a biopsy
and send it to Path.

23:31.061 --> 23:34.021
Menstruation, pregnancy,
ovarian cysts,

23:34.064 --> 23:35.849
menopause,
endometriosis...

23:35.892 --> 23:37.241
I want to know
what men get.

23:37.285 --> 23:38.504
All the research.

23:38.547 --> 23:40.244
Sounds like we make
a good team.

23:40.288 --> 23:42.464
Raaah!

23:42.508 --> 23:44.074
[ Clears throat ]

23:44.118 --> 23:48.122
♪♪

23:51.995 --> 23:53.649
I'm worried
about Richard.

23:53.693 --> 23:55.477
Because of the method?

23:55.521 --> 23:56.870
You thought it was
a good idea, right?

23:56.913 --> 23:59.612
It was.
For lap choles.

23:59.655 --> 24:02.615
We had a two-month-long waiting
list for patients in need.

24:02.658 --> 24:05.182
Then he extended it to more
complicated procedures.

24:05.226 --> 24:06.749
I wasn't here,
but he must have thought

24:06.793 --> 24:07.924
the residents
could handle it.

24:07.968 --> 24:10.492
Yeah,
that's what he said.

24:10.536 --> 24:12.538
He just screamed at me
that you and I

24:12.581 --> 24:14.583
don't get to have a say
because we weren't here.

24:14.627 --> 24:15.889
How did I get
dragged into this?

24:17.325 --> 24:20.328
Because I wasn't at
the M&M?

24:20.371 --> 24:22.939
I did sign off on it, and then
I wasn't there to defend it,

24:22.983 --> 24:25.202
so, yes, I'm sure he
feels like I abandoned him.

24:25.246 --> 24:26.943
He thinks we all did.

24:31.731 --> 24:34.124
Hey.
Want some coffee?

24:36.344 --> 24:37.519
Thank you.

24:39.173 --> 24:40.870
Did Owen run you out of
the room already?

24:40.914 --> 24:44.178
[ Laughs ]
He is the worst patient.

24:44.221 --> 24:47.660
I remember this one time
when he was 18 with the flu,

24:47.703 --> 24:49.923
I swear, the whining that was
coming out of his mouth,

24:49.966 --> 24:51.359
it was guttural.

24:51.402 --> 24:52.839
How's Farouk?

24:52.882 --> 24:54.536
He's so good.

24:54.580 --> 24:56.495
They weaned him off a few lines
already, and so far,

24:56.538 --> 24:58.453
he's tolerating
the anti-rejection meds.

24:58.497 --> 25:00.107
T-Teddy?

25:00.150 --> 25:01.369
What?

25:01.412 --> 25:03.110
[ Sighs ]

25:03.153 --> 25:05.547
Did did Owen
say anything to you?

25:05.591 --> 25:07.244
Or -- Or -- Or Hayes

25:07.288 --> 25:09.203
about what happened
in that car after I got out?

25:09.246 --> 25:12.467
Hayes came by to check on
Farouk, and he said goodbye.

25:12.511 --> 25:14.469
I think that near-death
experience,

25:14.513 --> 25:15.949
it made him want to --Owen's keeping something
from me,

25:15.992 --> 25:18.038
and it is big.

25:18.081 --> 25:20.388
For all I know, he's got a
secret wife in another country.

25:20.431 --> 25:21.694
[ Scoffs ]

25:21.737 --> 25:22.999
I'm serious.

25:23.043 --> 25:24.479
I mean... [scoffs]

25:26.263 --> 25:28.744
[ Sighs ]

25:28.788 --> 25:32.226
Owen confessed something,
Megan, to Hayes.

25:32.269 --> 25:34.489
It wasn't a near-death
experience that made Hayes quit.

25:34.533 --> 25:37.057
It's whatever Owen said to him
when he thought he was dying.

25:37.100 --> 25:39.450
Owen did something,
and if it's so big

25:39.494 --> 25:40.974
that he can't even
tell me...

25:41.017 --> 25:42.584
He probably
did do something.

25:42.628 --> 25:44.673
Come on. It's Owen.

25:44.717 --> 25:50.113
He's rash and stupid and
almost always...selfless.

25:50.157 --> 25:52.072
All of you almost died
to save Farouk.

25:52.115 --> 25:54.988
But, Owen, he --
he literally put himself last

25:55.031 --> 25:56.859
in order for that heart
to get here.

25:56.903 --> 25:59.470
He -- He chose to
end his life

25:59.514 --> 26:02.996
and went careening down a cliff
for us -- Farouk, me, you --

26:03.039 --> 26:04.998
and he would
do it again, Teddy.

26:05.041 --> 26:07.130
He always believes that he's
making the right decision,

26:07.174 --> 26:11.570
so whatever he did, whatever
he's doing...it's Owen.

26:11.613 --> 26:13.310
He must believe that
it's his only option.

26:13.354 --> 26:16.618
♪♪

26:21.318 --> 26:25.540
Link: Rongeur?

26:25.584 --> 26:27.455
Chief.
Always a pleasure.

26:27.498 --> 26:29.588
Hey, um, as soon as Perez
is done in here,

26:29.631 --> 26:32.329
I need him with Garrison
on an ex-lap in O.R. 5.

26:32.373 --> 26:34.288
I'm short
on residents today.

26:34.331 --> 26:36.203
Not a problem.
Almost done.Okay.

26:36.246 --> 26:38.292
Perez made a nice catch
on this patient.

26:38.335 --> 26:39.728
Caught a foot drop
that I missed.

26:39.772 --> 26:41.251
Spinal disc
herniation.

26:41.295 --> 26:42.949
Well, nice job, Perez.

26:42.992 --> 26:44.298
You seem to be the only one
who hasn't turned into

26:44.341 --> 26:46.953
a hapless intern
after the M&M.

26:46.996 --> 26:49.956
I caught it because
I examined her thoroughly.

26:49.999 --> 26:52.045
Excessive weight cancause
damage on the joints.

26:52.088 --> 26:54.047
True,
but you looked at Lila

26:54.090 --> 26:55.657
and decided she was
just a fat person.

26:55.701 --> 26:57.441
Fat people know they're fat.
You do not need to tell them.

26:57.485 --> 26:58.834
Of course not.

26:58.878 --> 27:00.270
But if the weight might be
making things worse --

27:00.314 --> 27:02.446
Might. Might be.
Obesity is a disease.

27:02.490 --> 27:06.059
It's not as easy for some of us
to lose weight as it is for you.

27:06.102 --> 27:08.583
[ Clears throat ] Sir.

27:08.627 --> 27:12.065
Sorry. I made a snap judgment
based on her history and BMI.

27:12.108 --> 27:13.893
Well, stop looking at the BMI.Excuse me?

27:13.936 --> 27:15.416
It's stupid.

27:15.459 --> 27:19.463
The Body Mass Index is
a fancy title and formula

27:19.507 --> 27:22.641
that was developed like 200
years ago by a mathematician.

27:22.684 --> 27:24.425
It doesn't account
for differences

27:24.468 --> 27:29.082
in the density of bones
or muscle tones or fat.

27:29.125 --> 27:32.085
It looks at numbers,
not distribution.

27:32.128 --> 27:35.871
So stop looking at it
and examine the patient.

27:35.915 --> 27:37.656
So why is it even
on the chart still?

27:37.699 --> 27:40.136
So insurance companies
can rob us blind.

27:40.180 --> 27:42.704
Hey, they charge higher premiums
for higher BMIs.

27:42.748 --> 27:44.663
Told you it was stupid.

27:44.706 --> 27:47.100
Now, let's hurry up.
I need Perez.

27:49.842 --> 27:51.234
Do you want to finish
the discectomy?

27:51.278 --> 27:53.149
Um, yes.

27:59.634 --> 28:01.201
Hey!

28:01.244 --> 28:04.857
So, I, um --
I just updated Francesca.

28:04.900 --> 28:08.295
We are going to
start her on

28:08.338 --> 28:10.819
a new low-dose, continuous
birth control, and, um, then --

28:10.863 --> 28:13.909
I know Link is
really angry with me.

28:13.953 --> 28:15.737
And I can hear
in your voice,

28:15.781 --> 28:18.566
which goes up an octave
every time I enter a room,

28:18.609 --> 28:20.611
that you are who
he's talking to about it.

28:20.655 --> 28:22.091
He's actually not.
It's okay.

28:22.135 --> 28:23.745
You're his best friend.

28:23.789 --> 28:26.313
I am grateful that he has
someone to talk to.

28:26.356 --> 28:29.490
But if it means that we can't
work together effectively,

28:29.533 --> 28:31.100
I need for you
to tell me that,

28:31.144 --> 28:33.233
because this was
awkward today,

28:33.276 --> 28:36.105
and our first responsibility
is to our patients.

28:36.149 --> 28:38.064
Okay?

28:38.107 --> 28:39.674
Thank you for
your help today.

28:50.163 --> 28:51.599
[ Clears throat ]

28:51.642 --> 28:54.776
Carina: So, my wife
works 24-hour shifts.

28:54.820 --> 28:57.387
If you want,
we can get coffee and talk.

28:57.431 --> 29:00.260
You are my boss.
Mm-hmm.

29:00.303 --> 29:01.740
But you're also
a very nice person

29:01.783 --> 29:05.091
who happened to
study the female orgasm.

29:05.134 --> 29:08.181
Casual sex is good,
right?

29:08.224 --> 29:10.444
Oh, I'm very
pro casual sex.

29:10.487 --> 29:12.663
With friends?

29:12.707 --> 29:14.187
Yeah, casual sex
with friends

29:14.230 --> 29:16.580
can be the best kind of
casual sex.

29:16.624 --> 29:20.236
A friend wants to take care of
your body, make you feel safe,

29:20.280 --> 29:24.414
and please you
all at the same time, so...

29:24.458 --> 29:27.330
Oh, but it's not
casual for you, is it?

29:27.374 --> 29:31.595
Okay. Wilson, if you love him,
you have to tell him,

29:31.639 --> 29:33.162
or you have to stop
having sex with him.

29:33.206 --> 29:34.816
Those are the only
two choices you have

29:34.860 --> 29:37.993
to give this friendship
a chance of surviving, okay?

29:38.037 --> 29:39.560
But before you do,

29:39.603 --> 29:42.824
check Wendy Costello's
incision in 1202.

29:45.609 --> 29:49.613
[ Door opens, closes ]

29:49.657 --> 29:51.398
[ Footsteps approaching ]

29:53.966 --> 29:55.968
Helm?

29:59.232 --> 30:00.973
You know, I was so busy
worried about

30:01.016 --> 30:04.019
what Schmitt did in that O.R.,
but you were in there, too.

30:04.063 --> 30:08.850
You're not okay, either,
and...I missed that.

30:08.894 --> 30:10.678
I'm sorry.

30:10.721 --> 30:12.767
I used to never
raise my hand in class,

30:12.811 --> 30:16.118
even though I always
had the right answer.

30:16.162 --> 30:19.818
All through elementary school,
I was so scared

30:19.861 --> 30:23.299
that people would hate me
or call me a know-it-all,

30:23.343 --> 30:25.606
so I just...

30:25.649 --> 30:26.955
didn't raise my hand.

30:29.653 --> 30:32.874
I thought
I outgrew it.

30:35.790 --> 30:38.837
[ Sighs ]

30:38.880 --> 30:40.839
I should have said something
to Levi.

30:40.882 --> 30:43.189
I could have stopped him
in that O.R.

30:43.232 --> 30:45.191
He would have listened to me.
I'm his best friend.

30:45.234 --> 30:48.890
It can be very hard
to speak up

30:48.934 --> 30:51.980
to people who are
so sure of themselves.

30:52.024 --> 30:58.117
But in that O.R.,
Schmitt was the lead surgeon.

30:58.160 --> 31:03.774
So he wasn't just your best
friend, he was your boss.

31:03.818 --> 31:06.081
Hmm?

31:06.125 --> 31:10.172
Yeah, I was kind of a
know-it-all, too, you know?

31:10.216 --> 31:11.913
I know.

31:11.957 --> 31:15.003
[ Laughs ]
Hard to believe.

31:15.047 --> 31:16.570
[ Chuckles ]

31:16.613 --> 31:19.268
♪ I've seen the light

31:19.312 --> 31:21.923
Okay.
[ Sighs ]

31:21.967 --> 31:25.448
♪ I've felt the darkness grow

31:25.492 --> 31:27.102
Webber:
I preach responsibility.

31:27.146 --> 31:30.976
I encourage people to take
the full consequences.

31:31.019 --> 31:35.023
I try and live my life
with personal accountability.

31:35.067 --> 31:38.897
Even if my intent was good,
it killed a man.

31:38.940 --> 31:40.899
Your intent was good,
Richard.

31:40.942 --> 31:45.729
♪♪

31:45.773 --> 31:48.341
Lines can blur,

31:48.384 --> 31:53.520
and sometimes good intentions
can cloud good judgment.

31:53.563 --> 31:55.348
I'm sorry
I wasn't here.

31:55.391 --> 31:57.393
I was gone
with good intentions.

31:58.568 --> 32:05.097
You three are the --
the closest I have to, um...

32:05.140 --> 32:07.229
Well, you know.

32:07.273 --> 32:11.016
The thought of disappointing you
is -- is unbearable.

32:11.059 --> 32:12.452
I wasn't disappointed,
Richard.

32:12.495 --> 32:15.150
I was mad.

32:15.194 --> 32:18.414
[ Chuckles ]
I was enraged.

32:18.458 --> 32:22.070
Not at you
or the Webber Method.

32:22.114 --> 32:24.768
I mean,
a little bit at you.

32:24.812 --> 32:27.554
Mostly, I was
enraged at myself.

32:27.597 --> 32:29.295
Because, suddenly,
I was right back there again,

32:29.338 --> 32:33.212
right there
where Schmitt was.

32:33.255 --> 32:36.432
And I have spent years
struggling with

32:36.476 --> 32:38.608
the appropriate amount of
accountability to take

32:38.652 --> 32:40.523
for Sabie's death
on my table.

32:40.567 --> 32:42.917
And, yes, the surgeon
holding the scalpel is the one

32:42.961 --> 32:45.180
who is
ultimately responsible,

32:45.224 --> 32:48.009
but if you discount all of
the other factors at play,

32:48.053 --> 32:52.492
then how does that
surgeon recover?

32:52.535 --> 32:55.060
How does that surgeon move
forward and heal other people?

32:55.103 --> 32:58.541
How does
that surgeon heal?

32:58.585 --> 33:01.153
What happened to Levi
is devastating.

33:01.196 --> 33:02.763
And to me.

33:04.983 --> 33:07.072
And it deserves to
be scrutinized

33:07.115 --> 33:10.989
from every single angle.

33:11.032 --> 33:12.425
[ Scoffs ]

33:12.468 --> 33:15.297
The world's changed.

33:15.341 --> 33:17.647
Medicine's evolved.

33:17.691 --> 33:22.913
These students are -- are unlike
any I've ever taught.

33:22.957 --> 33:28.876
And I just wanted to give them
something to...

33:28.919 --> 33:32.314
feel excited about
practicing medicine.

33:32.358 --> 33:36.536
But you are what's exciting
about them practicing medicine.

33:36.579 --> 33:38.451
They don't need a method.

33:38.494 --> 33:40.322
They just need you.

33:40.366 --> 33:42.498
♪♪

33:48.069 --> 33:52.943
Dr. Eisenburg, 4673.
Dr. Eisenburg, 4673.

33:52.987 --> 33:54.336
Hey.

33:54.380 --> 33:56.077
So, you're welcome.

33:56.121 --> 33:57.383
Perfect technique,
barely left a mark.

33:57.426 --> 33:58.601
Might be
my best work yet.

33:58.645 --> 34:00.081
Maybe it's Seattle.

34:00.125 --> 34:01.909
Maybe, or it's having
my favorite resident back.

34:01.952 --> 34:03.824
I'm not sure.[ Cellphone chimes ]

34:03.867 --> 34:05.565
You want to grab some dinner?
Celebrate my stellar work?

34:05.608 --> 34:06.696
Maggie: Hi.

34:06.740 --> 34:09.090
Hello.

34:09.134 --> 34:10.352
Hi.

34:10.396 --> 34:11.788
[ Quietly ] Sorry.

34:11.832 --> 34:13.051
For what?

34:14.356 --> 34:17.359
Um, Amelia Shepherd
and Maggie Pierce,

34:17.403 --> 34:18.534
this is Nick.

34:18.578 --> 34:20.101
These are my sisters.
Oh.

34:20.145 --> 34:22.277
Wow. Hi.

34:22.321 --> 34:23.496
Nice to meet you.Mm-hmm.

34:23.539 --> 34:25.498
Uh-huh.

34:25.541 --> 34:26.890
Um, I'm from Minnesota.

34:26.934 --> 34:29.110
Oh, are you on
the secret project?

34:29.154 --> 34:32.331
I would've noticed.[ Chuckles ]

34:32.374 --> 34:34.072
He has a post-op.

34:34.115 --> 34:35.377
I do have a post-op.Yeah.

34:35.421 --> 34:36.509
Very complicated
hernia repair.

34:37.553 --> 34:38.902
Okay.

34:38.946 --> 34:40.643
Nice to meet you.

34:40.687 --> 34:43.951
♪♪

34:43.994 --> 34:46.519
I have a thing...to go do.Hmm.

34:47.737 --> 34:51.350
[ Chuckles ]
I like Minnesota.

34:51.393 --> 34:54.135
It is...
full of surprises.

34:55.919 --> 34:57.573
I have a thing, too.

35:02.883 --> 35:04.276
[ Door opens ]

35:04.319 --> 35:05.799
Hey.
Hey.

35:05.842 --> 35:07.148
[ Door closes ]We're home,

35:07.192 --> 35:09.324
and we brought falafel.

35:09.368 --> 35:11.196
Oh, no.
I stopped by Nicoletti's.

35:11.239 --> 35:13.067
Oh, we got enough food
to feed a --

35:13.111 --> 35:14.416
You?

35:14.460 --> 35:16.375
[ Chuckles ] Maybe.

35:16.418 --> 35:18.072
[ Both chuckle ]

35:18.116 --> 35:21.510
I guess we should talk next time
before we do anything.

35:24.905 --> 35:27.168
[ Exhales deeply ]

35:27.212 --> 35:28.778
So, I misread something
at work today.
I've been
thinking about --

35:28.822 --> 35:30.084
Oh.

35:30.128 --> 35:31.651
You first.
You go ahead.

35:35.829 --> 35:38.266
Link...

35:38.310 --> 35:39.659
What is it?

35:42.183 --> 35:43.750
Link, I...

35:47.623 --> 35:49.103
We shouldn't have sex.

35:49.147 --> 35:51.323
Oh.

35:51.366 --> 35:53.194
♪♪

35:53.238 --> 35:54.761
Okay.

35:54.804 --> 35:59.635
♪♪

35:59.679 --> 36:01.115
Are you sure?

36:01.159 --> 36:03.509
Yes.

36:03.552 --> 36:05.598
Okay.

36:05.641 --> 36:07.817
[ Luna crying ]

36:07.861 --> 36:09.123
I will be right back.

36:09.167 --> 36:10.864
Do not eat
all the garlic bread.

36:10.907 --> 36:12.474
[ Chuckles ]

36:12.518 --> 36:14.520
[ Crying continues ]

36:14.563 --> 36:21.527
♪♪

36:23.224 --> 36:25.270
Can we talk?

36:25.313 --> 36:26.271
Yeah. Come in.

36:33.278 --> 36:36.063
I let you down.

36:36.106 --> 36:41.503
When you introduced the
Webber Method, I had concerns.

36:41.547 --> 36:44.941
But I decided to
trust in it,

36:44.985 --> 36:46.943
because it was you.

36:46.987 --> 36:49.119
And I know I --
I should have been

36:49.163 --> 36:50.686
more vocal about it
from the beginning.

36:50.730 --> 36:53.907
I should have said
something m-more.

36:53.950 --> 36:56.518
I-I should have
said m-more.

36:56.562 --> 36:59.173
It's okay, Bailey.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.696
You can say it.

37:03.264 --> 37:07.312
Despite
the physician shortage

37:07.355 --> 37:10.967
and the backlog
of surgeries,

37:11.011 --> 37:14.623
I feel, strongly,
that the Webber Method

37:14.667 --> 37:17.322
should not just be
suspended temporarily,

37:17.365 --> 37:18.888
but permanently.

37:18.932 --> 37:20.760
Understood.

37:20.803 --> 37:23.458
Oh, and --
and for the record...

37:23.502 --> 37:26.983
you did say something.

37:27.027 --> 37:31.249
And I had my wife
overrule you.

37:31.292 --> 37:34.252
It wasn't right,
and it wasn't fair,

37:34.295 --> 37:35.818
and I'm sorry I did it.

37:37.167 --> 37:43.826
♪ So, what do I do now?

37:43.870 --> 37:45.393
Meredith:
It's been said that

37:45.437 --> 37:48.353
a house divided against itself
cannot stand.

37:48.396 --> 37:51.181
Webber: Good night.♪ Sunrise

37:51.225 --> 37:53.880
But conflict on the road
to progress is inevitable.

37:53.923 --> 37:56.796
Nico:
Thanks, Mrs. Schmitt.

37:56.839 --> 37:58.537
[ Sighs ]

37:58.580 --> 38:00.016
Levi.

38:00.060 --> 38:01.888
My mom shouldn't
have called you.

38:01.931 --> 38:04.020
Please go away.

38:04.064 --> 38:06.849
Hey, look, we've --
we've all lost patients.

38:06.893 --> 38:08.808
I know it's hard,
but it's part of the job.

38:08.851 --> 38:10.810
But you got to
come back to work.

38:10.853 --> 38:12.899
I'm not going back there.What do you mean?

38:12.942 --> 38:14.204
If -- If --
If you don't come back,

38:14.248 --> 38:15.380
you're gonna lose
your residency spot and --

38:15.423 --> 38:16.772
Please go away.

38:16.816 --> 38:18.383
Levi --

38:18.426 --> 38:21.647
Please go away
and don't come back.

38:21.690 --> 38:23.301
We're done.

38:23.344 --> 38:27.609
♪ Before another day ends

38:27.653 --> 38:30.830
♪ Today I'll survive

38:30.873 --> 38:33.093
♪ Tomorrow,
I'll make sense of my life ♪

38:33.136 --> 38:37.489
And at least some division
is always a certainty.

38:37.532 --> 38:40.230
Because we all want what we
think is best for everyone.

38:40.274 --> 38:42.058
Teddy:
Owen, I just...

38:42.102 --> 38:45.192
♪♪

38:45.235 --> 38:47.716
Thank you, Dr. Hunt.

38:47.760 --> 38:52.112
♪ Our stories
will keep us alive ♪

38:52.155 --> 38:53.287
Teddy --
No.

38:53.331 --> 38:54.767
Teddy,
just leave it, okay?

38:54.810 --> 38:57.117
I can't.

38:57.160 --> 38:58.858
Teddy. Teddy!

38:58.901 --> 39:01.730
♪ Midday, I've grown
a little restless ♪

39:01.774 --> 39:06.518
And when we can trust at
least that much to be true...

39:06.561 --> 39:11.479
♪ But the strength of the sea
is tamed by the shore ♪

39:11.523 --> 39:12.959
Meredith: Hi.

39:13.002 --> 39:16.310
Bad timing, bad hallway,
bad sisters.

39:16.354 --> 39:17.746
[ Chuckles ]
No, no, no, it was fun.

39:17.790 --> 39:19.748
Was it?
Yeah, it was.

39:19.792 --> 39:22.316
It was fun.
Do you have
to leave tonight?

39:22.360 --> 39:24.100
I don't want to
leave you ever.

39:24.144 --> 39:25.319
♪ Our sacred ground
will cast out any doubt ♪

39:25.363 --> 39:26.712
[ Laughs ]

39:26.755 --> 39:28.148
I'm sorry.
Was that weird?

39:28.191 --> 39:29.454
That's --

39:29.497 --> 39:31.586
You know what?
Screw it.

39:31.630 --> 39:33.196
We're adults.
I don't care.

39:33.240 --> 39:36.199
I-I don't like leaving you.
I want to be with you.

39:36.243 --> 39:38.419
You know?

39:38.463 --> 39:39.942
Why don't you just come
with me on the red-eye

39:39.986 --> 39:41.814
and spend a few days
with me in Minnesota,

39:41.857 --> 39:43.293
and I'll come back
with you.

39:43.337 --> 39:46.296
As exhausting as that sounds,
I have the kids.

39:46.340 --> 39:49.430
And you know I used to
know everything

39:49.474 --> 39:51.519
that went on in there.

39:51.563 --> 39:53.739
And right now, I'm feeling
pretty disconnected

39:53.782 --> 39:56.437
from some people
that I'm very close to.

39:56.481 --> 39:58.265
Hamilton is recovering,

39:58.308 --> 40:00.963
so I think I'm going to
take advantage of that

40:01.007 --> 40:03.444
and just stay put
for a while.

40:03.488 --> 40:05.881
But for the record,

40:05.925 --> 40:07.927
I don't ever want to leave you,
either.

40:07.970 --> 40:11.539
And my children
are asleep.

40:11.583 --> 40:13.976
If you don'thave to
leave tonight...

40:14.020 --> 40:15.761
I don't.

40:15.804 --> 40:17.632
Then why are we
still standing here?

40:17.676 --> 40:19.155
I don't know.

40:19.199 --> 40:20.722
It's simply not realistic

40:20.766 --> 40:22.637
for any house
to avoid some division.

40:22.681 --> 40:24.900
♪ Sunset

40:24.944 --> 40:27.990
But how much division
can any house withstand...

40:28.034 --> 40:32.342
♪ Maybe it's all necessary

40:32.386 --> 40:38.871
♪ The holding on

40:38.914 --> 40:40.394
[ Car alarm chirps ]

40:40.438 --> 40:42.788
♪ The letting go Dr. Altman.

40:42.831 --> 40:44.398
Tell me what you just got out
of my husband's car,

40:44.442 --> 40:46.095
or I'm gonna have to
call the police.

40:46.139 --> 40:48.663
♪ And I'll take a deep breath

40:48.707 --> 40:50.491
...before it finally falls?

40:50.535 --> 40:53.755
♪ Let's get some rest

41:15.255 --> 41:23.132
